Makes: 8Ingredients:3 extra-large eggs250ml (1 cup) water250ml (1 cup) matzo mealOil, for frying200g (1 cup) sugar mixed with 15ml (1 tbsp) ground cinnamonMethod:1) Beat the eggs, water and matzo meal until smooth and runny.2) Heat some oil in a pan, pour in spoonfuls of batter and fry the pancakes, turning once, until golden brown on both sides.3) Serve immediately, dusted with cinnamon and sugar. Some people like to pour a little golden syrup on first, then add cinnamon and sugar. They're also delicious with fresh berries.